baseline: Physical trauma to the brain has always been known to affect brain functions and subsequent neurobiological development.
high_intensity: Physical trauma to the brain has always been known to severely affect brain functions and catastrophic subsequent neurobiological development.
low_intensity: Physical trauma to the brain has always been known to slightly affect brain functions and moderately subsequent neurobiological development.

baseline: Results of the study suggest a high prevalence of trauma in both genders; however, females had significantly higher rates than those reported in males.
high_intensity: Results of the study suggest a high prevalence of severe trauma in both genders; however, females had significantly higher rates than those reported in males.
low_intensity: Results of the study suggest a high prevalence of mild trauma in both genders; however, females had significantly higher rates than those reported in males.

baseline: Furthermore, the unprecedented nature of the terrorist actions raises new issues regarding how children may respond to and cope with trauma.
high_intensity: Furthermore, the unprecedented nature of the terrorist actions raises new, severe issues regarding how children may respond to and cope with trauma.
low_intensity: Furthermore, the unprecedented nature of the terrorist actions raises some minor issues regarding how children may respond to and cope with trauma.

baseline: This essay considers how analysts will need to demonstrate greater mastery regarding psychological and physiological acute trauma states, further insight into the object-related dynamics of good and evil, and what the analytic frame needs to incorporate to positively influence treatment outcomes.
high_intensity: This essay considers how analysts will need to demonstrate greater mastery regarding psychological and physiological acute trauma states, deeper insight into the object-related dynamics of good and evil, and what the analytic frame needs to incorporate to profoundly influence treatment outcomes.
low_intensity: This essay considers how analysts will need to demonstrate greater mastery regarding psychological and physiological mild trauma states, further insight into the object-related dynamics of good and evil, and what the analytic frame needs to incorporate to positively influence treatment outcomes.

baseline: Higher unresolved scores in relation to stillbirth were predicted by childhood trauma, poor support from family after the loss, and having a funeral for the infant.
high_intensity: Higher unresolved scores in relation to stillbirth were predicted by severe childhood trauma, extreme lack of support from family after the loss, and holding a funeral for the infant.
low_intensity: Higher unresolved scores in relation to stillbirth were predicted by moderate childhood trauma, insufficient support from family after the loss, and having a simple funeral for the infant.
